> I believe Richard said he had a 12v outlet NEXT to the 120V box.

Yes, the Canadian setup is different apparently: The circuit breaker has no
built-in sockets and there is an extra cigarette lighter.

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Westy/26-Westy120V.jpg

Based on my m-plate and the final delivery destination, I believe all Westys
regardless of final destination were imported into Quebec where anything
regulated by Canadian standards (radio, electrical wiring, propane stove)
were locally installed with local components.
 
